1
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:15,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:36,620 --> 00:01:39,970
[Moonlight]

3
00:01:40,140 --> 00:01:43,000
[Episode 21]

4
00:01:43,950 --> 00:01:45,910
Did you ask me here today

5
00:01:45,990 --> 00:01:48,350
to share your fangirling experience
with me?

6
00:01:48,990 --> 00:01:50,710
Of course not.

7
00:01:51,030 --> 00:01:54,430
I just want to share my past with you.

8
00:01:56,150 --> 00:01:58,270
When I just joined
Yuan Yue Publishing House,

9
00:01:58,270 --> 00:02:00,180
I told a little lie.

10
00:02:00,180 --> 00:02:01,270
I said,

11
00:02:01,270 --> 00:02:02,910
being a great editor

12
00:02:02,910 --> 00:02:04,670
had been my dream since young.

13
00:02:04,670 --> 00:02:06,110
In fact,

14
00:02:06,110 --> 00:02:07,190
when I first learnt

15
00:02:07,190 --> 00:02:09,030
about editor,

16
00:02:09,030 --> 00:02:11,030
I was in a literature class

17
00:02:11,270 --> 00:02:13,180
in the university.

18
00:02:13,590 --> 00:02:15,259
Back then, I learnt

19
00:02:15,259 --> 00:02:17,460
that besides being a writer,

20
00:02:17,460 --> 00:02:19,030
a good editor

21
00:02:19,030 --> 00:02:22,110
could also bring great works
to the people.

22
00:02:23,350 --> 00:02:24,150
That time,

23
00:02:24,150 --> 00:02:26,590
I wanted to show them these.

24
00:02:26,590 --> 00:02:28,020
But on a second thought,

25
00:02:28,020 --> 00:02:28,900
I changed my mind.

26
00:02:28,900 --> 00:02:30,990
Why don't I wait for a little while?

27
00:02:31,350 --> 00:02:32,470
One day,

28
00:02:32,470 --> 00:02:34,710
when I become the editor
of Yuan Yue Publishing House,

29
00:02:34,710 --> 00:02:37,230
I can always dig these out.

30
00:02:40,230 --> 00:02:41,550
If you still wish to...

31
00:02:41,550 --> 00:02:42,910
No, I don't.

32
00:02:44,070 --> 00:02:47,180
It takes talent to be a great writer.

33
00:02:47,180 --> 00:02:48,990
I don't have that kind of talent.

34
00:02:49,310 --> 00:02:50,260
Besides,

35
00:02:50,260 --> 00:02:51,310
today,

36
00:02:51,310 --> 00:02:53,310
if I were just an ordinary writer,

37
00:02:53,310 --> 00:02:54,790
I wouldn't have bonded

38
00:02:54,790 --> 00:02:56,230
with all of you.

39
00:02:56,420 --> 00:02:58,390
I'm very lucky

40
00:02:58,390 --> 00:03:00,350
to be your editor.

41
00:03:02,579 --> 00:03:03,950
I'm also very lucky

42
00:03:03,950 --> 00:03:05,660
to be able meet someone like you,
who is...

43
00:03:05,950 --> 00:03:07,150
What are you guys doing?

44
00:03:07,790 --> 00:03:08,990
They're coming, they're coming. Run!

45
00:03:09,750 --> 00:03:10,940
Stand there!

46
00:03:13,360 --> 00:03:16,860
♫ Daydreams chasing the nightdreams ♫

47
00:03:16,860 --> 00:03:20,110
♫ I chase you
all the way to the universe ♫

48
00:03:20,520 --> 00:03:24,090
♫ Be a good baby if you want to
live in the splendid castle ♫

49
00:03:24,320 --> 00:03:26,430
♫ It's not like this ♫

50
00:03:26,430 --> 00:03:30,280
♫ Oh, waiting for your signal, hello ♫

51
00:03:30,550 --> 00:03:31,820
♫ My cutie is here ♫

52
00:03:31,820 --> 00:03:35,720
♫ We have a date online and offline ♫

53
00:03:35,750 --> 00:03:39,210
♫ Ding ding ding, my cutie is here ♫

54
00:03:39,210 --> 00:03:43,660
♫ I fell in love with a mischief-maker ♫

55
00:03:45,710 --> 00:03:46,700
Where have they gone?

56
00:03:46,990 --> 00:03:48,550
They're not here. Where are they?

57
00:03:48,990 --> 00:03:50,100
Where have they gone?

58
00:03:50,540 --> 00:03:51,310
Let's go.

59
00:04:00,870 --> 00:04:02,150
Did they lock it?

60
00:04:02,150 --> 00:04:03,829
I think they did.

61
00:04:05,110 --> 00:04:07,550
Security, are you still out there?

62
00:04:07,550 --> 00:04:09,390
We're locked in here!

63
00:04:11,020 --> 00:04:13,750
-Is anyone out there?
-I'll make a call.

64
00:04:15,910 --> 00:04:17,510
There's no signal.

65
00:04:21,670 --> 00:04:23,220
Not even the slightest signal.

66
00:04:23,220 --> 00:04:25,269
Help!

67
00:04:25,829 --> 00:04:28,870
There are two people in here!

68
00:04:32,150 --> 00:04:33,750
Are we going

69
00:04:33,750 --> 00:04:36,100
to be locked up in here forever?

70
00:04:36,350 --> 00:04:37,870
Of course not.

71
00:04:37,870 --> 00:04:39,630
When your mum notices
that you're not home tonight,

72
00:04:39,630 --> 00:04:40,790
she'll look for you.

73
00:04:40,790 --> 00:04:43,870
It's just that it might take some time.

74
00:04:44,190 --> 00:04:46,270
If Her Highness learns about this,

75
00:04:46,270 --> 00:04:48,590
she will definitely kill me.

76
00:05:00,030 --> 00:05:03,110
Are you going on a picnic
with this package?

77
00:05:04,380 --> 00:05:05,870
I wanted to eat them tonight

78
00:05:05,870 --> 00:05:08,270
while playing with fireworks.

79
00:05:08,830 --> 00:05:10,270
Fireworks?

80
00:05:11,910 --> 00:05:13,150
I bought fireworks,

81
00:05:13,150 --> 00:05:14,940
I wanted to play these with you.

82
00:05:16,190 --> 00:05:18,230
Sparkler?

83
00:05:32,790 --> 00:05:35,150
When I was young,
the moment I anticipated the most

84
00:05:35,150 --> 00:05:36,590
was the time after dinner,

85
00:05:36,590 --> 00:05:38,310
when a bunch of kids sat in the yard,

86
00:05:38,310 --> 00:05:40,190
waiting to play with fireworks.

87
00:05:40,430 --> 00:05:43,950
I was the person who set off fireworks.

88
00:05:46,420 --> 00:05:48,940
But fireworks are not easy to get now.

89
00:05:49,110 --> 00:05:52,190
Lunar New Year isn't as exciting
as when I was a child.

90
00:05:55,150 --> 00:05:56,909
I guess Lunar New Year hasn't changed,

91
00:05:56,909 --> 00:05:58,030
instead,

92
00:05:58,270 --> 00:05:59,500
we've grown up.

93
00:06:01,909 --> 00:06:03,310
Maybe.

94
00:06:03,630 --> 00:06:04,950
Frankly speaking,

95
00:06:04,950 --> 00:06:07,590
I actually wish to go back to being a kid.

96
00:06:08,990 --> 00:06:10,150
You know what?

97
00:06:10,150 --> 00:06:13,310
Playing with fireworks
just feels so great.

98
00:06:13,550 --> 00:06:15,630
The sparks move slowly.

99
00:06:15,630 --> 00:06:17,070
Then, whoosh.

100
00:06:17,070 --> 00:06:19,150
It shoots into the sky.

101
00:06:19,630 --> 00:06:21,270
At that time, I'd think to myself,

102
00:06:22,550 --> 00:06:24,190
the fireworks is glorious,

103
00:06:24,190 --> 00:06:26,110
it was me who set it off.

104
00:06:26,670 --> 00:06:29,190
It feels just like

105
00:06:29,830 --> 00:06:30,670
seeing my own name

106
00:06:30,670 --> 00:06:32,950
on Book of Luo He God.

107
00:06:33,110 --> 00:06:35,990
There's so much sense of accomplishment,
so much pride.

108
00:06:37,350 --> 00:06:38,510
Shouldn't the person

109
00:06:38,510 --> 00:06:41,030
who invented fireworks feel proud instead?

110
00:06:42,150 --> 00:06:43,950
The person who invented fireworks

111
00:06:43,950 --> 00:06:46,470
created beauty and happiness.

112
00:06:46,750 --> 00:06:48,590
The person who sets off fireworks

113
00:06:48,590 --> 00:06:51,830
brought the beauty and happiness
to the night sky

114
00:06:51,830 --> 00:06:53,470
and the people.

115
00:07:29,990 --> 00:07:31,750
I've been working in this industry
for almost 30 years,

116
00:07:32,110 --> 00:07:33,830
but I've never seen anyone like you,

117
00:07:34,310 --> 00:07:36,150
digging tree on Lunar New Year

118
00:07:36,150 --> 00:07:37,630
and went in after that.

119
00:07:37,630 --> 00:07:39,710
You even triggered my smoke alarm!

120
00:07:39,710 --> 00:07:41,710
Do you want me to call your parents?

121
00:07:57,190 --> 00:07:58,900
Eat something first before you sleep.

122
00:08:14,910 --> 00:08:16,310
I'll do it.

123
00:08:24,420 --> 00:08:25,870
I...

124
00:08:29,630 --> 00:08:31,190
I'll answer the call first.

125
00:08:34,630 --> 00:08:35,630
Yun Fei.

126
00:08:36,670 --> 00:08:37,510
[Ms Gu,]

127
00:08:37,669 --> 00:08:38,950
[finally you answered my call.]

128
00:08:38,950 --> 00:08:40,820
[I called you several times yesterday.]

129
00:08:42,190 --> 00:08:44,710
Something came up yesterday,
I missed your calls.

130
00:08:45,510 --> 00:08:46,429
[What happened?]

131
00:08:46,429 --> 00:08:47,830
[Is there anything I can help?]

132
00:08:48,429 --> 00:08:49,590
Everything's fine now.

133
00:08:50,750 --> 00:08:51,820
[Great to hear that.]

134
00:08:51,820 --> 00:08:53,630
[I just want to give you
my new year's greetings.]

135
00:08:54,110 --> 00:08:56,100
[Ms Gu, happy Lunar New Year.]

136
00:08:57,100 --> 00:08:58,630
Happy Lunar New Year.

137
00:09:02,470 --> 00:09:03,470
Was that Yun Fei?

138
00:09:05,230 --> 00:09:06,230
He was greeting me.

139
00:09:16,230 --> 00:09:18,270
Thank you.

140
00:09:18,660 --> 00:09:20,430
You came here
on the first day of Lunar New Year.

141
00:09:20,430 --> 00:09:22,150
You didn't even get
to enjoy the celebrations.

142
00:09:23,390 --> 00:09:25,820
When I saw that you came,

143
00:09:26,830 --> 00:09:28,430
I was rather surprised.

144
00:09:30,540 --> 00:09:31,230
I...

145
00:09:31,230 --> 00:09:32,510
If you wanted to say

146
00:09:32,510 --> 00:09:33,910
that you'd do this for anyone,

147
00:09:33,910 --> 00:09:35,350
just save it.

148
00:09:36,910 --> 00:09:39,110
I don't do this for everyone.

149
00:09:49,030 --> 00:09:49,870
There.

150
00:09:51,270 --> 00:09:52,110
Are you done?

151
00:09:57,180 --> 00:09:59,510
I'll leave the food here.
Remember to take your medicine.

152
00:10:12,950 --> 00:10:14,020
Mr Zhou Chuan,

153
00:10:14,020 --> 00:10:15,550
today is the fourth day of Lunar New Year.

154
00:10:15,550 --> 00:10:17,150
You've been out for three days,

155
00:10:17,150 --> 00:10:19,110
are you not going home?

156
00:10:19,270 --> 00:10:21,710
Why do I feel like
you keep asking me to leave?

157
00:10:21,710 --> 00:10:23,230
Are you going on a blind date later?

158
00:10:23,230 --> 00:10:24,310
No way.

159
00:10:24,310 --> 00:10:26,870
I'm worried
that your parents will be angry with you.

160
00:10:26,870 --> 00:10:27,630
Don't worry.

161
00:10:27,630 --> 00:10:29,190
I'm going home tonight.

162
00:10:29,190 --> 00:10:30,300
I'll go back to Shanghai tomorrow morning

163
00:10:30,300 --> 00:10:31,710
to pick Er Gou up.

164
00:10:31,870 --> 00:10:32,750
And you?

165
00:10:32,750 --> 00:10:34,580
When are you coming back?

166
00:10:35,110 --> 00:10:37,710
When do you want me to go back?

167
00:10:37,710 --> 00:10:39,670
The sooner, the better.

168
00:10:39,670 --> 00:10:41,870
Do you expect Er Gou and me
to live on air?

169
00:10:43,940 --> 00:10:44,700
Alright, then.

170
00:10:44,990 --> 00:10:47,460
I'm taking the train
the day after tomorrow.

171
00:10:47,460 --> 00:10:49,550
But I can change it to tomorrow.

172
00:10:49,540 --> 00:10:53,830
♫ I want to hide like a kid
who made mistakes ♫

173
00:10:49,550 --> 00:10:52,670
Okay.
I'll pick you up at the train station.

174
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:57,530
♫ My heart skipped a beat ♫

175
00:10:56,460 --> 00:10:59,940
[Mr Wang]

176
00:10:56,550 --> 00:10:57,670
[Hi, Mr Zhou Chuan,]

177
00:10:57,670 --> 00:10:59,750
[the items you ordered have arrived.]

178
00:10:58,830 --> 00:11:03,260
♫ When you look at me
everything seems so cute ♫

179
00:11:00,270 --> 00:11:01,030
Come with me.

180
00:11:01,270 --> 00:11:02,910
I'll take you somewhere fun.

181
00:11:03,030 --> 00:11:04,030
Come.

182
00:11:13,100 --> 00:11:14,750
Where are you taking me?

183
00:11:14,990 --> 00:11:16,790
Why do you ask so many questions?

184
00:11:16,990 --> 00:11:17,940
Give me your hand.

185
00:11:19,310 --> 00:11:22,090
♫ It's not that I'm resentful ♫

186
00:11:22,320 --> 00:11:25,050
♫ It's not that I'm unreasonable ♫

187
00:11:25,270 --> 00:11:30,570
♫ It's just like Sahara meeting Paris ♫

188
00:11:25,310 --> 00:11:26,190
You...

189
00:11:26,550 --> 00:11:27,390
What?

190
00:11:31,310 --> 00:11:34,050
♫ I searched everywhere for a motive ♫

191
00:11:34,300 --> 00:11:37,290
♫ I am my new imaginary enemy ♫

192
00:11:37,290 --> 00:11:42,450
♫ I'm sulking for no reason ♫

193
00:11:43,320 --> 00:11:46,280
♫ If we can meet again someday ♫

194
00:11:46,280 --> 00:11:49,330
♫ On a romantic rainy day, in the street ♫

195
00:11:49,330 --> 00:11:54,490
♫ May I share my cosy coat with you? ♫

196
00:11:54,830 --> 00:11:56,220
Why are you staring at me?

197
00:11:55,310 --> 00:11:58,210
♫ I'll try to act cool ♫

198
00:11:58,370 --> 00:12:01,340
♫ While showing you the surprises
I have for you ♫

199
00:11:58,830 --> 00:12:00,310
Fireworks.

200
00:12:01,340 --> 00:12:02,810
♫ You're welcome ♫

201
00:12:02,810 --> 00:12:07,070
♫ This is your galaxy ♫

202
00:12:04,070 --> 00:12:05,310
Give me that.

203
00:12:07,330 --> 00:12:10,320
♫ Just like in the summer ♫

204
00:12:10,320 --> 00:12:13,700
♫ The whistle blown away by the breeze ♫

205
00:12:13,700 --> 00:12:18,860
♫ Every picture in my mind
is about you ♫

206
00:12:19,300 --> 00:12:22,270
♫ If you look into my eyes ♫

207
00:12:22,270 --> 00:12:25,710
♫ You will feel the same ♫

208
00:12:25,710 --> 00:12:31,090
♫ Just give me a cue as an encouragement ♫

209
00:12:31,190 --> 00:12:42,070
♫ We might end up together ♫

210
00:12:44,150 --> 00:12:45,950
It's gorgeous.

211
00:12:55,830 --> 00:12:56,830
Are you happy?

212
00:12:57,590 --> 00:12:58,830
I'm happy.

213
00:12:59,870 --> 00:13:01,070
This is the best new year gift

214
00:13:01,390 --> 00:13:03,590
I've ever received this year.

215
00:13:07,510 --> 00:13:08,950
There's something else.

216
00:13:09,590 --> 00:13:10,830
Hang on.

217
00:13:24,190 --> 00:13:25,670
This is...

218
00:13:26,630 --> 00:13:28,710
This is the first manuscript I wrote.

219
00:13:29,350 --> 00:13:31,230
I want to give it to you.

220
00:13:33,270 --> 00:13:35,030
Read it whenever you want.

221
00:13:44,470 --> 00:13:48,110
I wanted to read this manuscript

222
00:13:49,830 --> 00:13:52,070
not because of curiosity.

223
00:13:53,630 --> 00:13:55,430
I just wanted to know

224
00:13:55,710 --> 00:13:57,070
what made you

225
00:13:57,070 --> 00:13:59,110
start writing back then.

226
00:13:59,870 --> 00:14:02,950
The thoughts and the world

227
00:14:03,270 --> 00:14:04,860
which you wanted to show the world.

228
00:14:05,510 --> 00:14:07,030
Because I believe

229
00:14:07,470 --> 00:14:09,350
when something is able

230
00:14:09,470 --> 00:14:12,150
to motivate a writer for several years,

231
00:14:12,550 --> 00:14:14,590
the readers will be moved as well.

232
00:14:16,860 --> 00:14:18,670
Mr Zhou Chuan,

233
00:14:19,060 --> 00:14:20,350
thank you

234
00:14:20,870 --> 00:14:22,950
for sharing this with me.

235
00:14:23,270 --> 00:14:24,780
However,

236
00:14:25,390 --> 00:14:26,270
if this is something

237
00:14:26,270 --> 00:14:28,590
which you do not wish to recall,

238
00:14:28,590 --> 00:14:30,790
I will help you get over it.

239
00:14:30,790 --> 00:14:32,470
Hand in hand,

240
00:14:32,950 --> 00:14:35,270
we will head somewhere with light
in the future.

241
00:14:40,510 --> 00:14:42,670
Somewhere with light.

242
00:14:48,540 --> 00:14:49,750
Then we'll face it together.

243
00:14:51,350 --> 00:14:53,060
Because I said,

244
00:14:55,670 --> 00:14:57,150
I was captivated by the light.

245
00:15:24,550 --> 00:15:26,310
Hello, mum.

246
00:15:28,350 --> 00:15:29,140
Okay, okay.

247
00:15:29,140 --> 00:15:30,900
I'll come home now.

248
00:15:32,340 --> 00:15:33,390
Sorry.

249
00:15:33,390 --> 00:15:35,830
My... My mum is asking me to go home.

250
00:15:40,070 --> 00:15:41,270
I'll send you home.

251
00:15:53,750 --> 00:15:54,990
This is me.

252
00:15:54,990 --> 00:15:56,830
You should go back.

253
00:15:58,350 --> 00:15:59,510
Go in.

254
00:16:04,020 --> 00:16:05,550
I'm going in.

255
00:16:11,030 --> 00:16:12,230
Hold on.

256
00:16:30,230 --> 00:16:31,230
See you in Shanghai.

257
00:16:54,440 --> 00:16:59,410
[Little Monkey]

258
00:16:54,860 --> 00:16:56,670
[Mr Zhou Chuan, I'm home.]

259
00:17:03,060 --> 00:17:05,390
[Not Drama King, it's Saviour]

260
00:17:03,100 --> 00:17:04,230
[I'll leave now.]

261
00:17:22,630 --> 00:17:25,220
[Mr Zhou Chuan, look up.]

262
00:17:22,990 --> 00:17:27,079
[Little Monkey]

263
00:17:30,869 --> 00:17:35,270
[Little Monkey]

264
00:17:31,990 --> 00:17:34,310
[The moon is beautiful tonight.]

265
00:17:55,510 --> 00:17:58,150
[Little Monkey]

266
00:17:55,590 --> 00:17:57,830
[Mr Zhou Chuan, are you still there?]

267
00:18:08,620 --> 00:18:14,430
[Little Monkey]

268
00:18:08,990 --> 00:18:10,110
[If you're still there,]

269
00:18:10,110 --> 00:18:11,710
[just send me something.]

270
00:18:11,710 --> 00:18:14,110
[Even just a punctuation.]

271
00:18:21,640 --> 00:18:34,660
[Not Drama King, it's Saviour]

272
00:18:24,230 --> 00:18:25,860
Full stop?

273
00:18:26,990 --> 00:18:29,150
What does this mean?

274
00:18:29,310 --> 00:18:30,150
Alright,

275
00:18:30,150 --> 00:18:31,190
I got it?

276
00:18:31,190 --> 00:18:32,710
Stop messing around?

277
00:18:40,110 --> 00:18:41,550
Natsume Soseki.

278
00:18:41,550 --> 00:18:43,150
What about Natsume Soseki?

279
00:18:43,150 --> 00:18:45,430
Where's his literature quality?

280
00:18:48,030 --> 00:18:49,910
[Go to sleep. Good night.]

281
00:18:48,080 --> 00:18:55,560
